Privacy Policy

Hallyu Style ("we", "our", "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application. Please read this privacy policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this privacy policy, please do not access the app.

1. Information We Collect
We may collect and process the following types of information:

a. Personal Data
When you register or make purchases through Hallyu Style, we may collect personal details such as:

Name
Email address
Phone number
Shipping and billing address
Payment information (secured via third-party payment gateways)
b. Device Information
We may collect information about your device, including:

IP address
Device ID
Operating system and browser type
Location (with your consent)
c. Camera Access
If you grant permission, we may use your device’s camera to enable features like product photography (uploading images for reviews or virtual try-on). The images captured are only used for the specific purpose and are not stored by us.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information collected for the following purposes:

To process and deliver orders
To improve customer service
To send updates about your orders or app usage
To enhance your shopping experience
To manage your account
For analytics and market research
To provide technical support
To comply with legal obligations
3. How We Share Your Information
We may share your information with third parties only in the following cases:

Service Providers: To third-party vendors who help us operate the app (e.g., payment processors, delivery services).
Legal Requirements: If required by law, we may disclose your information in response to a subpoena or other legal request.
Business Transfers: If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.
4. Your Consent for Camera Usage
Hallyu Style requests access to your device’s camera to offer certain functionalities, including:

Uploading photos for product reviews
Virtual try-on for products (if available)
We will ask for your explicit consent before accessing the camera. You may disable camera permissions in your device settings if you choose not to allow access.

5. Data Retention
We retain your personal data for as long as necessary to provide our services and fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy. Once the data is no longer required, we will delete it or anonymize it unless required by law.

6. Security of Your Information
We implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information. Your data is encrypted and securely stored. However, please note that no transmission over the internet is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee the security of your data.

7. Your Data Rights
You have the right to:

Access the personal information we hold about you
Request corrections or updates to your personal information
Withdraw your consent to data collection at any time (e.g., by disabling camera permissions)
Request deletion of your personal data, subject to certain conditions
8. Children’s Privacy
Hallyu Style is not intended for users under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we learn we have collected personal data from a child without parental consent, we will delete it.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal obligations. Any changes will be posted in the app, and we encourage you to review this policy periodically.

10. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, you may contact us at:
Email: privacy@hallyustyle.com
Address: 123 K-Pop Street, Seoul, South Korea
